The Province of Quebec is issuing a 30billion yen eurobond due May 7, 1997 paying five pct and pricedat 102-1/2 pct, lead manager Bank of Tokyo International Ltdsaid.    The non-callable bond is available in denominations of onemln yen and will be listed in Luxembourg. The sellingconcession is 1-1/4 pct, while management and underwritingcombined pays 3/4 pct.    The payment date is May 7. REUTER&#3;